  "learn": {
    "heading": "How long division works",
    "intro": "<p>Long division repeats four small steps: <strong>divide</strong> (how many times does it fit?), <strong>multiply</strong>, <strong>subtract</strong>, then <strong>bring down</strong> the next digit. Knowing your facts makes each step quick.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>84 ÷ 4:</strong> 4 fits into 8 two times (8 ÷ 4 = 2). Then 4 fits into 4 once. Answer = <strong>21</strong>. Check: 21 × 4 = 84. ✔",
      "Estimate first: 84 ÷ 4 is about 80 ÷ 4 = 20, so an answer near 21 makes sense."
    ]
  },
